439
00:30:32,545 --> 00:30:33,610
Well, Mariel has hers.

440
00:30:35,932 --> 00:30:37,492
Yeah, but Mariel came back whole.

441
00:30:39,587 --> 00:30:42,289
Everyone we know of, so far, anyway, has come back whole.

442
00:30:53,629 --> 00:30:55,084
I'm sorry if I got you into trouble with my dad.

443
00:30:56,026 --> 00:30:57,739
No, no, no, it's not your fault.

444
00:30:59,338 --> 00:31:04,521
It was inappropriate for me to be sharing the things with you that I did.

445
00:31:06,502 --> 00:31:10,671
But, you know, I've just never been that close with people,

446
00:31:11,868 --> 00:31:13,468
especially after I lost the arm.

447
00:31:15,257 --> 00:31:18,340
People were always like,"oh, poor guy."

448
00:31:20,978 --> 00:31:21,499
I hate that.

449
00:31:22,524 --> 00:31:23,021
I know.

450
00:31:24,162 --> 00:31:25,114
People have always treated me like,

451
00:31:25,149 --> 00:31:27,739
"poor orphan girl, lost her mom."

452
00:31:30,140 --> 00:31:30,937
It sucks.

453
00:31:34,592 --> 00:31:35,705
Look, I want you to know that

454
00:31:35,740 --> 00:31:38,445
even if we don't get to see each other much anymore,

455
00:31:38,480 --> 00:31:41,267
I believe everything you said.

456
00:31:42,820 --> 00:31:44,764
I believe that you getting your arm back was a miracle.

457
00:31:45,864 --> 00:31:47,047
I'm sorry my father didn't.

458
00:31:49,256 --> 00:31:49,636
Thank you.

459
00:31:51,158 --> 00:31:51,729
It's his problem.

460
00:31:53,881 --> 00:31:55,459
I tried talking to Mariel about it,

461
00:31:55,494 --> 00:31:58,086
but I think I just made her uncomfortable.

462
00:32:03,870 --> 00:32:04,326
Lewis...

463
00:32:07,257 --> 00:32:08,514
I want to know what's in the water.

464
00:32:09,923 --> 00:32:11,292
Good or bad, I want to know about it,

465
00:32:12,520 --> 00:32:13,927
'cause I've always felt different, too.

466
00:32:15,830 --> 00:32:17,428
I mean, people have accepted me...

467
00:32:19,331 --> 00:32:21,136
and I've even been popular,

468
00:32:23,414 --> 00:32:25,773
but I've never really felt like I belonged anywhere...

469
00:32:28,436 --> 00:32:29,693
not even in my own family.

470
00:32:31,149 --> 00:32:32,369
And it's just getting worse.

471
00:32:32,404 --> 00:32:35,448
I mean, I feel like they're part of this secret club, you know?

472
00:32:36,554 --> 00:32:37,998
And they just don't want me to be a part of it.

473
00:32:41,120 --> 00:32:41,538
Yeah.

474
00:32:46,336 --> 00:32:51,489
You know, Kira, you might want to talk to father Scanlon about all this.

475
00:32:51,524 --> 00:32:53,223
He runs the hurricane survivor group,

476
00:32:54,176 --> 00:32:56,533
- and they've all had similar exper...
- Lewis.

477
00:33:03,094 --> 00:33:05,883
- I promised Mariel that we'd finish tonight.
- It's all right. I was just leaving.

478
00:33:10,070 --> 00:33:11,669
- Good night, Lewis.
- Night, Kira.

479
00:33:13,876 --> 00:33:14,411
See ya.

480
00:33:21,511 --> 00:33:22,806
So you two work everything out?

481
00:33:24,938 --> 00:33:26,232
